What to do if your computer has been hacked

Reset your passwords
Log out of all online accounts
Disconnect from the internet
Remove external hard drives
Scan your computer for malware and viruses
Wipe your hard drive (if necessary)
Install security software
Closely monitor your credit and financial accounts


Reasons why you were hacked in the first place
Avoid opening suspicious email attachments. 
Make sure your operating system (OS) is up to date
Use strong passwords, including numbers, letters, and punctuation

How to avoid being targeted by computer hackers 

Maintain strong passwords
Use VPN at all times
Keep files backed up
Ensure your firewall is properly configured
